Act 118 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: S2/11/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1199
4
5 By: Representative Barker
6 By: Senator J. Bryant
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO REPEAL THE STATUTE CONCERNING THE
10 PROHIBITION AGAINST A SCHOOL DISTRICT BOARD OF
11 DIRECTORS GRANTING A LEGAL TRANSFER UNDER CERTAIN
12 CONDITIONS; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
13
14
Subtitle
15
16 TO REPEAL THE STATUTE CONCERNING THE
17 PROHIBITION AGAINST A SCHOOL DISTRICT
18 BOARD OF DIRECTORS GRANTING A LEGAL
19 TRANSFER UNDER CERTAIN CONDITIONS.
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
22
23 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 6-18-317 is repealed.
24 6-18-317. Prohibited transfers.
25 (a) Boards of directors of local school districts are prohibited from
26 granting legal transfers under ยง 6-18-316 when:
27 (1) Either the resident district or the receiving district is
28 under a desegregation-related court order; and
29 (2) The transfer in question would violate the court order.
30 (b) Each form filed with the Division of Elementary and Secondary
31 Education reporting a legal student transfer must be accompanied by an
32 affidavit signed by each member of both school district boards of directors
33 stating that the transfer does not violate the prohibition set forth in
34 subsection (a) of this section.
35 (c) If the transfer fails to comply with subsection (b) of this
36 section, the division shall withhold from each district state aid in an
*TNL100*
